Greetings to Kim Jong Il, Kim Yong Nam and Pak Pong Ju from Chinese Party and State Leaders 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il and Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, and Pak Pong Ju, premier of the DPRK Cabinet, received a message of greetings from Hu Jintao, General Secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, President of the People's Republic of China and chairman of the Central Military Commission of China, Wu Bangguo, chairman of the Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress, and Wen Jiabao, premier of the State Council of China, on September 8 on the occasion of the 58th anniversary of the DPRK.
 The message said:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We extend sincere congratulations and best wishes to you and, through you, to the Workers' Party, the government and the people of Korea on behalf of the Communist Party, the government and the people of China on the occasion of the 58th anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The foundation of the DPRK opened a new chapter for the Korean people to build a state as masters of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people steadily propelled the development of the economic community and foreign relations in the spirit of self-reliance and fortitude under the leadership of President Kim Il Sung, General Secretary Kim Jong Il and the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We sincerely wish the Korean people steady, fresh and greater success in accomplishing the cause of building a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 China and the DPRK are friendly neighboring countries linked by mountain and rivers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sino-Korean friendship overcame the trials of history as it was provided and developed by the elder revolutionaries of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the new period and under the new situation the Chinese side hopes for bringing greater happiness to the two countries and the two peoples by steadily advancing the long-standing Sino-Korean friendly and cooperative relations together with the Korean side in the spirit of "inheriting tradition, facing the future, continuing good neighborliness and enhancing cooperation".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We wish the DPRK prosperity and the Korean people happiness.

Greetings to Kim Jong Il from Russian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a message of greetings from V. Putin, Russian president, today on the occasion of the 58th anniversary of the DPRK.
 The message says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Democratic People's Republic of Korea, an independent and sovereign state, was founded in Korea on September 9, 1948. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many important and significant events have since then taken place in the relations between our two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today friendship and cooperation between Russia and the DPRK is full of new contents and reaching a higher stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I am convinced that the dialogue between our states will make a great contribution to peace, stability and security in the Korean Peninsula and the rest of Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Your Excellency Kim Jong Il &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I wish you good health and greater success in your responsible state work and hope that the friendly DPRK will achieve new success in socio-economic development of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sincerely yours.

Message of Greetings from Cuban Leader 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il and Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, received a message of greetings from Raul Castro Ruz, second secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Cuba, first vice-president of the Council of State and first vice-president of the Council of Ministers, on Sept. 8 on the occasion of the 58th birthday of the DPRK.
 The message said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dear comrades, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It gives me particular pleasure to send warmest congratulations to the fraternal WPK, government and people of the DPRK on behalf of the Cuban party, government and people on the occasion of the 58th anniversary of the founding of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I would like to take this opportunity to reiterate our unequivocal support to the Korean people in their just struggle to defend the sovereignty of the country and achieve the peaceful reunification of the Korean nation and reaffirm our firm will to steadily boost the fraternal bonds, solidarity and cooperation between the parties, governments and people of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dear comrades, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Please accept my best wishes for the heroic Korean people's prosperity and welfare as well as successes in your work and happiness. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Highest regards and warm greetings to you.

Homage Paid to Kim Il Sung 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- Senior officials of the party, the army and the state and people from all walks of life visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace on Sept. 9 to pay homage to President Kim Il Sung on the occasion of the 58th anniversary of the DPRK.
 Senior officials of the Workers' Party of Korea, the army and the state, chairpersons of the friendly parties, Cabinet members, deputies to the Supreme People's Assembly in Pyongyang, leading officials of the party and power organs, public organizations, ministries and national institutions entered the hall where the statue of the President stands. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amid the solemn playing of "Song of General Kim Il Sung", a floral basket in the joint name of the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the WPK, the DPRK National Defence Commission, the Presidium of the DPRK SPA and the DPRK Cabinet was laid before the statue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbons of the floral basket were letters "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung Is Immortal".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Senior officials of the Party, the army and the state paid their respects to the statue of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They entered in humble reverence the hall where the President lies in state. They made vows to him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then they walked round orders, medals, certificates of honorary titles awarded to the President in our country and from different countries, the portrait of the smiling President and bronze relievos in the Mourning Hall, a train coach he used during his on-the-spot guidance and visits to foreign countries and a car he used in the last moments of his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters, officials of organs at all levels and people from all walks of life visited the memorial palace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the diplomatic corps and the military attaches corps here and overseas Koreans including a congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan for the celebration of the 58th anniversary of the DPRK headed by Ko Tok U, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan, visited the palace to pay homage to the President.

Banquet Given in Celebration of DPRK Birthday 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- The DPRK government arranged a banquet at the People's Palace of Culture on Saturday evening in celebration of the 58th birthday of the DPRK.
 Present there were senior officials of the party, the army and the state, chairperson of friendly party, Cabinet members, deputies to the Supreme People's Assembly in Pyongyang, leading officials of party, military and power organs, social organizations, ministries and national institutions, anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters, officials in the fields of science, education, culture and art, public health and the press, former unconverted long-term prisoners who are the patriotic champions of reunification, heroes and heroines and persons of distinguished service. Attending it were also players of the DPRK team which won the 3rd FIFA U-20 Women's World Championship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were overseas compatriots including a congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan which is staying here to celebrate the DPRK birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation were diplomatic envoys of different countries, members of the military attaches corps and representatives of international organizations here and other foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The banquet was addressed by Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The foundation of the DPRK by President Kim Il Sung was the birth of a genuine sovereign state of the people, the first of its kind in the long history of the Korean nation, and the great historical event which brought about a radical change in carving out the destiny of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is opening a heyday of prosperity, glorifying the dignity and might of Juche Korea century after century under the tested and seasoned leadership of Kim Jong Il, genius of politics and military affairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK, which has taken the road of victory and glory as it has Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il at the head of revolution, will prosper as ever under the uplifted banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK government will positively strive to implement the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration, the embodiment of the idea of "By our nation itself," smash the moves of the separatists at home and abroad, surely achieve the historic cause of national reunification and build a free, peaceful new world with no aggression and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK, which has the might of the single-minded unity of the army and the people around the leader as well as matchless and ever-victorious self-defensive war deterrent, will mercilessly shatter any political, military and economic offensives of the enemies and invariably create an ever-victorious history in accomplishing its just cause.

Floral Baskets Laid before Portraits of Kim Il Sung in Cuba
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Havana, September 8 (KCNA) -- Floral baskets were placed before the portraits of smiling President Kim Il Sung with due ceremony at the Organization of Solidarity of the Peoples of Africa, Asia and Latin America and Kim Il Sung Economic Special School in Cuba on September 6 and 7 on the occasion of the 58th birthday of the DPRK.
 Present there were the secretary general and members of the organization, the vice-president of the Cuban Institute of Friendship with the Peoples, the chairman of the Cuban Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification, the rector, teaching staff and students of the special school and the DPRK ambassador and staff members of the embassy in Havana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants placed the floral baskets before the portraits and paid tribute to the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary general of the organization said that the participation of many people in the celebrations of the DPRK's birthday was an expression of solidarity with the Korean people, adding that the organization would always extend full support to the cause of Korea's reunification.

U.S. Oceanic Strategy for Aggression under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists pursue an aim of military and strategic importance to attack the anti-imperialist independent countries with oceans as theatres. This is the essence of their Asian-Pacific strategy.
 Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed article slamming the U.S. oceanic strategy for aggression to put the Asia-Pacific under its control. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In their strategy of attaching importance to the Asia-Pacific aimed at realizing their world domination the U.S. imperialists regard Northeast Asia, the Korean Peninsula in particular, as their important strategic stronghold, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They seek to form a front against the anti-imperialist independent countries including the DPRK on the seas linking Japan, south Korea, etc. and deploy naval forces equipped with nukes in a bid to blockade straits, mount preemptive nuclear attacks on them and, furthermore, conduct landing operations against them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They intend to use Japan and south Korea bounded on three sides by the sea as important bases for carrying out their oceanic strategy from which to launch aggression against the continent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The spearhead of the oceanic strategy pushed forward by the U.S. imperialists in the Asia-Pacific is directed to the Korean Peninsula at present. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is the main theatre of the global military and political confrontation at present. This is because the U.S. made the DPRK a principal target of the U.S. strategy for world domination, its conception of building a unipolar world. It is a strategic goal of the U.S. to start another Korean war in the 21st century come what may in a bid to seize the peninsula. The Korean Peninsula is the area where the interests of its neighboring big powers are intertwined. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Once a war breaks out on the peninsula these countries will not remain passive onlookers to it. In case of a crisis on the peninsula the response of these countries to it will be bound to affect the development. In a word, the second Korean war to be provoked by the U.S. imperialists would mean a new world war. Their oceanic strategy is being pushed forward according to this war scenario. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The situation on the peninsula and the rest of the Asia-Pacific is getting tenser due to the reckless war moves of the U.S. imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The peace-loving people of Asia and the rest of the world are called upon to see through the sinister aim pursued by their oceanic strategy and wage a positive struggle to frustrate it.

National Day Celebrated
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- The 58th founding anniversary of the DPRK was significantly celebrated on Saturday.
 The fourth national agricultural workers' contest in dancing to peasant music was held in the Rungrado Recreation Ground in Pyongyang. It was strong in national flavor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A dancing party of members of the Korean Democratic Women's Union was held in the plaza of the Tower of the Juche Idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Art performances were given at theatres in the capital and local areas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary drama "Blood at an International Conference" was performed by artistes of the State Theatrical Company at the State Theatrical Theatre, a performance "May Country Prosper" by artistes of the Mansudae Art Troupe at the Ponghwa Art Theatre and a performance by artistes of the State National Art Troupe at the Central Youth Hall. Concerts were staged by artistes of the State Symphony Orchestra and the brass band of the Yun I Sang Music Institute at the Moranbong Theatre and the Yun I Sang Concert Hall. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Acrobatic performances were given at the Pyongyang Circus Theatre and the Circus Theatre of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Provincial art troupes also presented their performances to delight working people and youths and students in North Phyongan Province, Ryanggang Province, Kangwon Province and other provinces marking the national day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 People from all walks of life across the country spent the holiday with diverse cultural and sports events. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Merry singing and laughter of working people and school youth and children were heard all day long from the cultural and recreation grounds in Pyongyang which have been spruced up such as the holy place of revolution Mangyongdae, Moran Hill and the Rungrado Recreation Ground. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An art performance of workers and trade union members of provincial level institutions was given in Chongjin City, North Hamgyong Province, and art performances of members of women's union organizations in Ryanggang Province and South Phyongan Province took place in Hyesan and Phyongsong respectively. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Agricultural workers in Hamhung City, South Hamgyong Province, had a football match, a volleyball match, a contest in dancing to peasant music and so on.

Ore Dressing Plant Commissioned
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 10 (KCNA) -- A ceremony of commissioning the ore dressing plant of the Ryonghung Mine was held on the spot Saturday.
 It was attended by Paek Hyon Bong, chairman of the Korean Committee for the Promotion of Economic Cooperation with Foreign Countries, officials concerned and officials and employees of the mine. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present were members of the delegation of the Chinese Guangshou Group Co., Ltd. headed by Director General Huang Guoqing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Congratulatory speeches were followed by a report on the commissioning of the plant. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter said that a new concentrated ore production base has been completed to start its operation thanks to the positive efforts of the committee and the group company. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The commissioning of the plant marks a significant event in the relations of economic cooperation between the DPRK and China, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants looked round the ore dressing plant. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A reception was given in connection with the commissioning of the plant.

58th Birthday of DPRK Observed in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- Meetings were held in New Delhi, Kiev, Cairo and Sofia on Sept. 2 and 3 to celebrate the 58th founding anniversary of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 On display at the venues of the meetings were photos showing the glorious revolutionary history and undying exploits of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il and introducing the struggle of the Korean people to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The editor of the Public News of India said at the meeting that the foundation of the DPRK was a historical event of weighty significance in shaping out the destiny of the Korean people. He highly praised the immortal feats of Kim Il Sung who defeated the Japanese imperialists, achieved the liberation of Korea and founded the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that thanks to the seasoned and energetic leadership of Kim Jong Il who inherited the gifts of Kim Il Sung the DPRK is demonstrating its dignity and might despite the complicated international situation and all sorts of difficulties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary general of the Egypt-Korea Friendship Association noted that Kim Il Sung, the greatest man, had led the social revolution of different stages and the Fatherland Liberation War to victory and built a socialist system centering on the popular masses in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stressed that Kim Jong Il is demonstrating the might of the DPRK with his Songun politics, upholding the idea and intention of Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Messages of greetings to Kim Jong Il were adopted at meetings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, seminars and film shows were held in Egypt, France and Indonesia from Aug. 29 to 31 on the occasion of the anniversary.

Congratulatory Message to Kim Jong Il
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a congratulatory message from the Central Committee of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front (AINDF) on September 9, the 58th anniversary of the foundation of the DPRK.
 The message says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 58-year history of the DPRK was the period of victory and glory in which it has broken through all sorts of challenges and difficulties and preserved and glorified the revolutionary character of a socialist state centering on the popular masses under the leadership of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il. It was the annals of creation and change in which the DPRK has brought great changes and miracles in the revolution and construction and rushed toward the high peak of a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sacred history and traditions of the DPRK which has emerged victorious under the leadership of the President are now being creditably carried forward by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is standing up as a fortress of reunification as Kim Jong Il, peerless patriot, provided the June 15 joint declaration, landmark of independent reunification, and is wisely leading the movement for national reunification with his unique political caliber and boundless magnanimity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As it is led by Kim Jong Il with matchless grit and pluck, the DPRK is steering the world politics, standing against the U.S. that is styling itself the "only super power" in the world. The international authority and influence of the DPRK are increasing with each passing day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK, great in politics, matchless and ever-victorious in the military field and promising in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation as it is led by Kim Jong Il, illustrious commander of Mt. Paektu, is a genuine homeland of all Koreans and a beacon of hope for the south Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will uphold Kim Jong Il's idea of national reunification and leadership, bearing in mind the firm confidence that the dawn of a great prosperous powerful reunified state is breaking as it is led by him, destiny and future of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will more dynamically model the ranks of the AINDF on the Juche idea and help the people from all walks of life positively support, defend and uphold the patriotic Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will conduct a more vigorous patriotic movement for independent reunification, peace against war and great national unity in the idea of "By our nation itself" to decisively smash the undisguised moves of the U.S. imperialists to stifle the DPRK and the ambition of the pro-U.S. right-wing conservative forces to come to power again so as to open a new phase of national reunification.

Anti-U.S. Rally Held in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration reportedly held an "anti-U.S., anti-war rally to force the U.S. troops out of south Korea 61 years after their occupation" in Seoul on September 6.
 Displayed in the venue were posters denouncing the U.S. war drills against the north and the materialization of the "strategic flexibility" of the U.S. troops in south Korea and indicting them for criminal acts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the rally speakers condemned the U.S. troops for standing in the way of the Korean nation's movement for reunification and scheming to permanently occupy south Korea after they stepped in this land under the signboard of "liberator." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present reality, in which the relocation of the U.S. troops and the expansion of their bases in south Korea are in full swing in parallel with the unabated U.S. hostile policy towards the north, more deeply convinces the people from all walks of life of the importance and urgency of the struggle to drive the U.S. troops out of south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the participants staged a "10 million-men signature campaign against the shackling south Korea-U.S. alliance and for the withdrawal of the U.S. troops from south Korea" and an oratorical meeting to denounce the U.S.

Congratulatory Letter to Kim Jong Il from Chongryon Central Standing Committee
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a congratulatory letter from the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) today on the occasion of the 58th anniversary of the DPRK.
 The letter said that the Korean people have created a new era of national prosperity and social progress with the powerful political weapon for the accomplishment of the revolutionary cause of Juche since their glorious homeland, the DPRK, was founded on September 9, Juche 37 (1948). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the officials of Chongryon and Koreans in Japan more keenly feel the honor and pride of being overseas citizens of Juche Korea led by Kim Jong Il on the occasion, it said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It expressed the will to stand firm against the unprecedented anti-DPRK and anti-Chongryon moves of the Japanese authorities and ultra-right reactionaries to protect the motherland and resolutely defend the democratic national rights of Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also expressed the determination to make a tangible contribution to the independent reunification and prosperity of the country as required by the prevailing situation and work harder to boost the friendship with the Japanese people and international solidarity.

Papers Observe 58th Birthday of DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- Pyongyang-based papers Saturday dedicate editorials to the 58th birthday of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 President Kim Il Sung led the anti-Japanese revolutionary war to brilliant victory, achieved the national cause of the country's liberation and founded the DPRK on the basis of the firm historical root, Rodong Sinmun says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The foundation of the DPRK put an end to the distress-torn history of the Korean nation and helped the Korean people successfully realize their century-old desire to lead a dignified life as the masters of their destiny, genuine masters of the state and society.
 The President devoted all his life to glorifying the DPRK as the genuine country of the people, a powerful socialist nation, regarding "believing in the people as in Heaven" as his maxim. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will never forget the undying feats the President performed in building the state and his august name will shine for all ages as the banner of the dignity and prosperity of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has entered a new historic period in which it makes a leap forward towards a great prosperous powerful nation as it has great brilliant commander of Songun Kim Jong Il at its head. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the unshakable faith of Kim Jong Il to eternally glorify the DPRK as a powerful socialist nation admired by the whole world true to the President's cause of building a prosperous powerful country. The President's idea and feats of building a socialist state have been firmly defended, a heyday of the country's prosperity greeted and the might of Songun Korea intensified by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The great victory in the struggle for defending socialism in the 20th century and the miraculous successes gained in building a great prosperous powerful nation in the new century are the lofty fruition of the energetic Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The dignity and might of the DPRK led by him have reached the highest level. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the powerful war deterrent built on the road for Songun the DPRK has always won only victories in the political and military confrontation with the U.S. imperialists and the struggle for national prosperity and advanced the socialist cause in its own way with its own view. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Although the U.S. imperialists have resorted to vicious moves to slander the DPRK and check the advance of Korean-style socialism, the pluck of the Korean army and people is firm and their faith to staunchly advance along the road of independence is unshakable. As long as there is the Songun leadership of   Kim Jong Il the DPRK will demonstrate its dignity as an invincible and ever-victorious country that no enemy dare provoke. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson notes that the proud history of the DPRK is brilliantly going on under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il.

Dignity and Might of DPRK Shining in World
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- Though the DPRK has a small territory and population, its people have become the greatest people and the DPRK is demonstrating its dignity in the world as a powerful socialist country of Juche as they have a great leader, stresses Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article.
 Kim Jong Il is leading the Korean revolution to victory, demonstrating the dignity and authority of Juche Korea to the world with his tested leadership, distinguished political ability and intense devotion for the people, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The servicepersons and people are working world-startling miracles and innovations in all parts of the country with immense readiness and determination to bring about creation and change in this land, true to the idea and leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The marvelous changes in the DPRK are the shining fruition of his original Songun politics and Songun revolutionary leadership. The Korean people have not only defended socialism from the imperialists' vicious military blackmail and moves of aggression but made greater progress and won the fierce confrontation with them. The might of the single-minded unity of the revolutionary ranks of the DPRK has increased in every way. The DPRK has turned into an ideologically, politically and militarily strong power thanks to his wise leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A great leader is a source of a great people and a dignified country. This is the truth which the Korean people have keenly felt in pushing ahead with socialist construction, pulling through the tempest of revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il is the destiny of the country, people and socialism and symbol of all victories. His Songun politics serves as the all-powerful treasured sword and invincible banner.

Floral Baskets Laid before Monument to Victory in Korean War
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- Floral baskets were placed before the Monument to Victory in the Fatherland Liberation War Saturday on the occasion of the 58th birthday of the DPRK.
 Present at the floral basket-laying ceremony were senior officials of the Party, the army and the state, officials of the Party and power organs, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amid the playing of the floral basket-laying music a floral basket in the joint name of the Central Committee and Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea was laid before the statue "Victory," main theme of the monument. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then placed there were floral baskets in the name of the working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions and educational, public health and media organs and Party and power organs and enterprises in the city.

Wreaths Laid at Cemeteries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid at the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong and the Patriotic Martyrs Cemetery this morning on the occasion of the 58th birthday of the DPRK.
 Seen on wreath-laying stands were wreaths from General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the wreath-laying ceremonies were Party and state cadres and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wreaths were laid at the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong in the name of the Central Committee of the WPK, the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK and the Cabinet of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A wreath was also laid at the Patriotic Martyrs Cemetery in the joint name of the Central Committee of the WPK, the SPA Presidium of the DPRK and the DPRK Cabinet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wreaths were laid at the cemeteries from working people's organizations, ministries, national institutions and educational, public health and the press institutions and party and power bodies, enterprises, farms, etc. in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Bouquets were laid before the bust of Kim Jong Suk, anti-Japanese war hero at the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wreaths were laid before the statues of martyrs, monuments to and graves of the fallen fighters of the People's Army across the country on the same day.

Floral Baskets Laid before Kim Il Sung's Statues
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- Floral baskets were laid before the statues of President Kim Il Sung across the country on the occasion of the 58th birthday of the DPRK.
 People from all walks of life, school youth and children in Pyongyang visited his statue on Mansu Hill. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Standing before his statue was a floral basket sent by General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amid the playing of the floral basket-laying music floral baskets in the name of party and power bodies, public organizations, ministries, national institutions and scientific, educational, culture and art, public health and the press institutions, factories, enterprises, farms, schools, etc. and bouquets and flowers were laid before his statue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A floral basket was also laid in the name of the Pyongyang Mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Floral baskets were laid before the statues of the President at Kim Il Sung University, the Korean Film Studio, the Pyongyang Schoolchildren's Palace and other places of Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 People and school youth and children across the country visited the statues of the President in their residential quarters to lay floral baskets, bouquets and flowers before them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the consul general and members of the consulate general of China in Chongjin laid bouquets before the statue of the President in Chongjin and made a bow on Saturday, the 58th anniversary of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day Chinese delegations staying in Chongjin laid floral baskets before his statue and made a bow.

Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Unit
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 9 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected KPA Unit 1824.
 He congratulated the servicepersons of the unit on celebrating the DPRK's birthday with signal success in their combat and political training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He learned about the unit's performance of duty before watching its servicepersons' training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After watching the training he set forth important tasks which would serve as guidelines for bolstering the KPA as invincible revolutionary armed forces, expressing great satisfaction over the fact that all the servicepersons have grown to be a match-for-a hundred fighters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The hearts of all the servicepersons of the KPA are replete with the ardent love for the party, the leader, the country and the people and burning with towering hatred for the enemy, he said, adding that the country will imposingly stand as an invulnerable bulwark of socialism and our Juche-oriented revolution will win one victory after another it has such matchless ranks of fighters fully prepared politically and ideologically and in military technique. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He took deep care of the service and living of the soldiers, going round different places of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was greatly satisfied to see all the entertainment, educational and supply service facilities arranged well and the compound of the barracks and their surroundings kept neat and tidy. Noting that the servicepersons of the unit have distinguished themselves in its management by following the lifestyle of the anti-Japanese guerillas, he highly appreciated their assiduous way of managing the economic life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He gave the servicepersons of the unit a pair of binoculars and an automatic rifle as gifts before having a photo session with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Ri Myong Su, Hyon Chol Hae and Pak Jae Gyong and Ri Yong Chol and Ri Jae Il, first vice department directors of the C.C., the WPK.
